SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 568
By Briggs
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Joe Carson upon
winning a gold medal in the National Senior
Olympic Games.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should specially recognize those citizens who, through
their remarkable efforts, have distinguished themselves as exemplary athletes of whom we can
all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy individual is Joe Carson of Concord, who recently
brought great honor to this State by winning a gold medal at the 2025 National Senior Olympic
Games held in Des Moines, Iowa; and
WHEREAS, competing in the 70-plus age division, Mr. Carson captured gold on the 3-
on-3 Senior Olympic basketball team, demonstrating remarkable stamina, endurance, and
competitive spirit; and
WHEREAS, Joe Carson and his teammates competed against eighteen teams within
their age bracket to emerge on top with the gold medal; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Carson serves as an example of vitality and dedication to the people of
Tennessee, and he should be duly recognized for the boundless energy and remarkable talent
he brings to all his chosen endeavors, athletic and otherwise; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Joe Carson upon his
outstanding success in winning a gold medal in the 2025 National Senior Olympic Games and
for his lifetime of athletic achievement, as we extend to him our best wishes for every future
success and happiness.
